<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-61-1099 </DOCNO><TEXT>Two basic problems of spectral theory of Schroedinger operators H=-{Delta}+V(x)on the 2-sphere S/sub 2/ are studied: (Direct problem) calculate large-kasymptotics of eigenvalue clusters {{lambda}/sub kj/}/sub j/ in termsof the potential function V; (Inverse problem) recover V from asymptoticsof eigenvalue clusters. We get an explicit solution of the inverse problemand establish local spectral rigidity for zonal potentials V.</TEXT></DOC>